  "text": "The Kubernetes kubelet (pkg/kubelet/) contains four major sig-node components that manage the pod and container lifecycle:\n\n## 1. Pod Lifecycle Manager\nThe pod lifecycle manager consists of multiple components working together:\n- **Pod Manager** (pkg/kubelet/pod/pod_manager.go): The `Manager` interface and `basicManager` implementation track and manage all pods on the kubelet, maintaining mappings between static pods and their mirror pods. The `NewBasicPodManager()` function creates the pod manager instance.\n- **Pod Workers** (pkg/kubelet/pod_workers.go): Implements the pod synchronization lifecycle through `UpdatePodOptions` and `KillPodOptions`, managing pod creation, updating, and termination cycles.\n- **Lifecycle Handlers** (pkg/kubelet/lifecycle/handlers.go): The `handlerRunner` struct executes lifecycle hooks (pre-start and post-start hooks) for containers through the `NewHandlerRunner()` factory.\n\n## 2. Container Runtime Interface (CRI) Client\n**KubeRuntime Manager** (pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/kuberuntime_manager.go): The `kubeGenericRuntimeManager` struct implements the CRI interface. Created via `NewKubeGenericRuntimeManager()`, it manages container lifecycle operations including sandbox creation, container startup, image management, and logging. It communicates with container runtimes through gRPC services (RuntimeService and ImageManagerService from k8s.io/cri-client/pkg).\n\n## 3. Volume Manager\n**Volume Manager** (pkg/kubelet/volumemanager/volume_manager.go): The `VolumeManager` interface and `volumeManager` struct orchestrate volume attachment, detachment, mounting, and unmounting. Key components include:\n- `NewVolumeManager()`: Creates the volume manager instance\n- **Desired State of World Populator** (pkg/kubelet/volumemanager/populator/desired_state_of_world_populator.go): The `desiredStateOfWorldPopulator` tracks which volumes should be mounted based on pod specifications\n- **Reconciler** (pkg/kubelet/volumemanager/reconciler/reconciler_common.go): The `reconciler` struct continuously reconciles desired versus actual volume states, triggering attach/detach and mount/unmount operations\n\n## 4. Device Plugin Manager\n**Plugin Manager** (pkg/kubelet/pluginmanager/plugin_manager.go): The `PluginManager` interface and `pluginManager` struct manage device plugin registration and lifecycle. Created via `NewPluginManager()`, it uses desired/actual state of world pattern similar to the volume manager, with a plugin watcher populating desired state and a reconciler managing plugin registration/deregistration.\n\n## Integration Point\nAll these components are instantiated and orchestrated by the main **Kubelet** struct in pkg/kubelet/kubelet.go, created through `NewKubelet()`. The kubelet coordinates these managers to provide a complete pod execution environment with container runtime integration, volume management, and device plugin support."
}

